</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">I did some research on the anlaytics part and instead of only showing activeness of the class and level of question each student asks 
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">we can categorise the response in this 4 categories 
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="">The logic is built on a Hidden Metadata Engine: as students chat, the AI categorizes their thinking into four dimensions—Logic, Systems, Narrative, and Spatial—and awards XP to their profile using hidden tags. I am and will  build the Standard-Adaptive Logic (prompt ) , which ensures that a Class 3 student receives foundational examples while a Class 10 student receives technical, exam-oriented explanations.</span></span><span class=""><span class="x3nfvp2 xxymvpz xlshs6z xqtp20y xexx8yu x1uc92m x18d9i69 x181vq82 x12lo8hy x152skdk" aria-hidden="true"><span class="x1c4vz4f x2lah0s xn6xy2s"></span><span class="x1c4vz4f x2lah0s">4:14 pm</span></span></span></div></div><div class="x10l6tqk x1d37e2g x7308am"><div class="x1bvqhpb xx3o462 xuxw1ft x78zum5 x6s0dn4 x12lo8hy x152skdk"><span class="x1rg5ohu x16dsc37" dir="auto"><span class="x193iq5w xeuugli x13faqbe x1vvkbs xt0psk2 x1fj9vlw xhslqc4 x1hx0egp x1pg5gke xjb2p0i xo1l8bm xl2ypbo x1ic7a3i" style="--x-fontSize: 12px; --x-lineHeight: 8.5313px;">4:14 pm</span></span><div class="xhslqc4 x1rg5ohu x7phf20"><span aria-hidden="false" aria-label=" Delivered " data-icon="msg-dblcheck" class=""><svg viewBox="0 0 16 11" height="11" width="16" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" class="" fill="none"><title>msg-dblcheck</title><path d="M11.0714 0.652832C10.991 0.585124 10.8894 0.55127 10.7667 0.55127C10.6186 0.55127 10.4916 0.610514 10.3858 0.729004L4.19688 8.36523L1.79112 6.09277C1.7488 6.04622 1.69802 6.01025 1.63877 5.98486C1.57953 5.95947 1.51817 5.94678 1.45469 5.94678C1.32351 5.94678 1.20925 5.99544 1.11192 6.09277L0.800883 6.40381C0.707784 6.49268 0.661235 6.60482 0.661235 6.74023C0.661235 6.87565 0.707784 6.98991 0.800883 7.08301L3.79698 10.0791C3.94509 10.2145 4.11224 10.2822 4.29844 10.2822C4.40424 10.2822 4.5058 10.259 4.60313 10.2124C4.70046 10.1659 4.78086 10.1003 4.84434 10.0156L11.4903 1.59863C11.5623 1.5013 11.5982 1.40186 11.5982 1.30029C11.5982 1.14372 11.5348 1.01888 11.4078 0.925781L11.0714